2953.Name: Laideronnette
2953.SpawnTrigger: After 30 minutes (Earth minutes)  of continuous Rain.
2953.Tips: If the 30 minutes (Earth minutes) have already passed when her timer opens, she has a chance of spawning right away (probably).

2954.Name: Wulgaru
2954.SpawnTrigger: Chance to spawn when initiating battlecraft or  Grand Company leves.
2954.Tips: Leves do not need to be completed and can be safely abandoned.

2955.Name: Mindflayer
2955.SpawnTrigger: Moving over spawn points after 12 AM ET on the 2nd night of new moon.
2955.Tips: If he's not spawned on the 2nd night of new moon, he can be spawned after 5pm ET on the 3rd night.

2956.Name: Thousand-Cast Theda
2956.SpawnTrigger: Chance to spawn when successfully catching the big fish Judgeray.
2956.Tips: Judgerays can only be caught using the Wildfowl Fly bait at the Fallgourd Float fishing spot between 5 PM and 9 PM. For more detailed fishing information check: http://ff14angler.com/fish/218

2957.Name: Zona Seeker
2957.SpawnTrigger: Chance to spawn when successfully catching the big fish Glimmerscale.
2957.Tips: Gilmmerscales can only be caught using the Butterworm bait at the Nophica's Wells fishing spot during Clear Skies and Fair Skies. For more detailed fishing information check: http://ff14angler.com/fish/237

2959.Name: Lampalagua
2959.SpawnTrigger: Chance to spawn when initiating battlecraft or Grand Company leves.
2959.Tips: Leves do not need to be completed and can be safely abandoned.

2960.Name: Nunyunuwi
2960.SpawnTrigger: Do not let any fates fail for one real world hour.
2960.Tips: FATEs started by NPCs must be completed as well. If the NPC disappears, it is counted as failure.

2962.Name: Croque-mitaine
2962.SpawnTrigger: Chance to spawn when gathering Grade 3 La Noscean Topsoil (Unspoiled mining node at 7 PM, slot 8).
2962.Tips: Node lasts 3 hours ET. It is possible to keep the node open longer than its normal duration by opening it and waiting to gather.

2963.Name: Croakadile
2963.SpawnTrigger: Moving over spawn points after 5 PM during a full moon.
2963.Tips: Croakadile will only spawn at night. Full moon periods begin at 12 PM ET. Accordingly, it will be ready to spawn the moment night begins at 5 PM. Due to the length of its timer, it will spawn every other full moon.

2964.Name: The Garlok
2964.SpawnTrigger: After 200 minutes of dry weather have passed.
2964.Tips: If the 200 minutes have already passed when he becomes spawnable, he has a chance of spawning right away.

2965.Name: Bonnacon
2965.SpawnTrigger: Chance to spawn when gathering La Noscean Leek (Unspoiled botany node at 8 AM, slot 6).
2965.Tips: Node lasts 3 hours ET. It is possible to keep the node open longer than its normal duration by opening it and waiting to gather.

2966.Name: Nandi
2966.SpawnTrigger: Moving over spawn points with a minion summoned.
2966.Tips: Minions are still considered summoned while mounted.

2967.Name: Chernobog
2967.SpawnTrigger: Chance to spawn when a player dies.

2968.Name: Safat
2968.SpawnTrigger: Chance to spawn when a player reaches low HP.
2968.Tips: The easiest method to reach low HP is to take high falling damage.

2969.Name: Agrippa the Mighty
2969.SpawnTrigger: Chance to spawn when completing treasure maps.
2969.Tips: Toadskin, Boarskin, Peisteskin, and Leather Buried Treasure Maps, as well as Alexandrite Maps can have treasure located in Mor Dhona. (Note that Leather Treasure Map are NOT Leather Buried Treasure Maps.) Mysterious Maps become purchasable from Auriana in Revenant's Toll for 75 Poetics after completing the quest "Morbid Motivation" which is part of the Novus step of the ARR Relic quest line.

4374.Name: Kaiser Behemoth
4374.SpawnTrigger: Moving over spawn points with the Behemoth Heir minion summoned.
4374.Tips: Minions are still considered summoned while mounted. The Behemoth Heir minion is purchasable from Ardolain  for 400 Centurio Seals in The Forgotten Knight in Ishgard.

4375.Name: Senmurv
4375.SpawnTrigger: Complete the FATE "Cerf's Up" 5 times in a row.
4375.Tips: The FATEs "Cerf's Up", "El Miacid", "Elephant in the Brume", and "Special Tarasque Force" all block each other. Clearing them may yield faster occurrences of "Cerf's Up".

4376.Name: The Pale Rider
4376.SpawnTrigger: Chance to spawn when completing treasure maps.
4376.Tips: Only Wyvernskin Maps can have treasure located in The Dravanian Hinterlands.

4377.Name: Gandarewa
4377.SpawnTrigger: Chance to spawn when gathering Aurum Regis (Folklore mining node at 2 AM/PM, slot 6) or Seventh Heaven (Folklore botany node 4 AM/PM, slot 1).
4377.Tips: Nodes last 2 hours ET. It is possible to keep the node open longer than its normal duration by opening it and waiting to gather. Tomes of Geological and Botanical Folklore - Dravania are purchasable from the Splendors Vendor in Idyllshire for 50 Rowena's Token (Blue Gatherers' Scrip) each.

4378.Name: Bird of Paradise
4378.SpawnTrigger: Chance to spawn when the B Rank Squonk uses the action "Chirp".

4380.Name: Leucrotta
4380.SpawnTrigger: Kill 50 Allagan Chimeras, 50 Lesser Hydras, and 50 Meracydian Vouivres.

5984.Name: Okina
5984.SpawnTrigger: Spawns during full moon after enough Naked Yumemis (100) and Yumemis (100) have been killed.
5984.Tips: You can kill the mobs before the actual moon phase, if its random timer is ready it will spawn instantly at 12pm ET on the first day of full moon.

5985.Name: Gamma
5985.SpawnTrigger: Moving over spawn points at night with the Toy Alexander minion summoned.
5985.Tips: Minions are still considered summoned while mounted. The earliest Gamma will spawn is 5 PM. The latest Gamma will spawn is potentially 8 AM. There are no confirmed spawns past that time. The Toy Alexander minion is obtainable from Alexander - The Soul of the Creator (Normal and Savage).

5986.Name: Orghana
5986.SpawnTrigger: Complete the FATE "Not Just a Tribute" and move over spawn points.
5986.Tips: "Not Just a Tribute" is blocked by the FATE "Live for the Mettle".

5988.Name: Bone Crawler
5988.SpawnTrigger: Chance to spawn when using the chocobo porter.
5988.Tips: Will spawn at about the halfway point during the trip. Some routes are still being tested, but it is likely any route works.

5989.Name: Salt and Light
5989.Tips: You must use the discard action 50 individual times.
